            ContentJson = """{"passingScore":80,"questionsPerQuiz":8,"shuffleOptions":true,"showExplanationsAfterSubmit":true,"questions":[{"id":"cr1","text":"A customer calls to report defective parts from a recent order. What is the first step to handle this in Forge?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Create a job on the board titled 'Rework' and assign it to production"},{"id":"b","text":"Log a customer return, choosing the customer, the original job, and the reason for the return","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Open the sales order and change its status to Returned"},{"id":"d","text":"Send the customer a credit memo and close the issue"}],"explanation":"The right first step is to log a customer return. That records the RMA, gives it a number, ties it to the original job and customer, and starts it at the Received stage."},{"id":"cr2","text":"What are the five stages of a customer return, in order?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Open, Inspecting, Reworking, Complete, Archived"},{"id":"b","text":"Received, In Inspection, Rework Ordered, Resolved, Closed","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Created, Pending, In Progress, Done, Closed"},{"id":"d","text":"Submitted, Reviewed, Approved, Fulfilled, Closed"}],"explanation":"Returns go Received, then In Inspection, Rework Ordered, Resolved, and finally Closed. Not every return hits every stage — one can go from Received straight to Resolved if no inspection or rework is needed."},{"id":"cr3","text":"When you log a return and ask for a rework job, what happens automatically?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The original job is moved back to its first production stage"},{"id":"b","text":"A new job is created with a '[Rework]' prefix, at High priority, on the same track as the original, and linked to it","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The customer gets an automatic email about the rework"},{"id":"d","text":"The return is resolved automatically because rework was ordered"}],"explanation":"Asking for a rework job creates a new job titled with a '[Rework]' prefix, at High priority, on the same track and with the same assignee, starting at the first stage. It is linked to the original job, and the return moves to Rework Ordered."},{"id":"cr4","text":"You try to close a return that is at the Rework Ordered stage. What happens?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"It closes fine, since any return can be closed"},{"id":"b","text":"The system blocks it, because only resolved returns can be closed","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"It closes, but the rework job stays open on the board"},{"id":"d","text":"The system resolves the return first, then closes it"}],"explanation":"Only resolved returns can be closed. Trying to close one that is not resolved is blocked. You have to resolve the return first, then close it."},{"id":"cr5","text":"What do automatically generated RMA numbers look like?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"RET-YYYY-NNNN (year plus a sequence)"},{"id":"b","text":"RMA-XXXXX (for example, RMA-00001), assigned in order and padded to 5 digits","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"CR-NNN (a simple 3-digit counter)"},{"id":"d","text":"You type the RMA number in yourself when logging the return"}],"explanation":"RMA numbers look like RMA-XXXXX (for example, RMA-00001 or RMA-00042). The system takes the highest existing number, adds one, and pads it to 5 digits. You cannot set or change the number yourself."},{"id":"cr6","text":"Who can work with customer returns?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Any signed-in user can view and manage returns"},{"id":"b","text":"Admins, Managers, and Office Managers only","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Admins only — returns are sensitive"},{"id":"d","text":"Admins, Managers, Office Managers, PMs, and Engineers"}],"explanation":"Only Admins, Managers, and Office Managers can work with customer returns. Engineers and production workers cannot manage returns directly, though they may work the rework jobs that show up on the board."},{"id":"cr7","text":"You want to see the returns for one specific customer. How do you do it?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Filter the returns list by that customer, and optionally by stage","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Look under the customer's own page — returns live only there"},{"id":"c","text":"There is no filter; you have to scan the whole list by eye"},{"id":"d","text":"Export the full list and filter it in a spreadsheet"}],"explanation":"The returns list lets you filter by customer, and you can add a stage filter too. The newest returns show first."},{"id":"cr8","text":"A return has been inspected and the inspector wrote up their findings. What does the return keep track of?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Only the person's name and a pass-or-fail result"},{"id":"b","text":"Who inspected it, when they inspected it, and their inspection notes","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Only a reviewer's initials and a review date"},{"id":"d","text":"Just the general notes field — there is no separate place for inspection"}],"explanation":"A return records three inspection details: who inspected it, when they inspected it, and their inspection notes (up to 2000 characters). These are kept separate from the general notes field."},{"id":"cr9","text":"You try to resolve a return that has already been closed. What happens?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"It goes back to Resolved, since resolving overrides closing"},{"id":"b","text":"The system blocks it, because a closed return cannot be resolved","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"A brand-new RMA is created in the Resolved stage"},{"id":"d","text":"Nothing happens — resolving a closed return is simply ignored"}],"explanation":"You cannot resolve a return that is already closed; the system blocks it. Closed is the final stage and nothing more can change once you reach it."},{"id":"cr10","text":"When a rework job is created from a return, what does its description say?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"A copy of the original job's description"},{"id":"b","text":"A short note recording the RMA number and the reason for the return","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"'Rework required', with no other context"},{"id":"d","text":"Nothing — it's left blank for the assignee to fill in"}],"explanation":"The rework job's description records the RMA number and the return reason, for example 'Rework for RMA-00003. Reason: Parts out of tolerance on bore diameter'. That way anyone who sees the job on the board knows right away where it came from and why."}]}"""
        });

